OL,3,CMan stole #400,000 from in-laws'
OL,4,Cbusiness to fund 'lavish lifestyle'
OL,6,FA 46-year-old man has been found
OL,7,Fguilty of taking nearly #400,000 from
OL,8,Fa business owned by his wife's family
OL,9,Ffollowing a seven-day trial at
OL,10,FJersey's Royal Court.
OL,12,FThe 12-person jury found Benjamin
OL,13,FMitton guilty of one count of larceny
OL,14,Fas a servant - a worker stealing from
OL,15,Ftheir employer - and two counts of
OL,16,Ftransferring criminal property.
OL,18,FThe Court heard that, between March
OL,19,F2015 and July 2019, Mitton stole
OL,20,Faround #398,000 from Jersey scrap
OL,21,Fmetal company Hunt Bros Ltd.
