OL,3,CMan stole #400,000 from in-laws'
OL,4,Cbusiness to fund 'lavish lifestyle'
OL,6,FCrown Advocate Mike Preston,
OL,7,Fprosecuting, told the Court how the
OL,8,Fbusiness operated on trust between
OL,9,F"loving and caring family members".
OL,11,FMitton, he said, "abused that trust in
OL,12,Fthe most callous way, enriching
OL,13,Fhimself to the detriment of his own
OL,14,Ffamily".
OL,16,FThe Crown's case was that he used the
OL,17,Fcompany's cash to fund a "lavish
OL,18,Flifestyle with holidays in St Lucia,
OL,19,Fcruises, flights here, there and
OL,20,Feverywhere".
