OL,3,CMan stole #400,000 from in-laws'
OL,4,Cbusiness to fund 'lavish lifestyle'
OL,6,FMitton, the prosecution said, told the
OL,7,Fbank "a pack of lies" about the funds
OL,8,Fcoming from his own business in
OL,9,Fmanufacturing marine chain and sash
OL,10,Fwindow weights.
OL,12,FFor the defence, Advocate Greg Herold-
OL,13,FHowes, said there were "inadequacies
OL,14,Fin the financial processes" at Hunt
OL,15,FBros Ltd - describing the firm's
OL,16,Frecords as "demonstrably unreliable".
OL,18,FThe defence argument was that the
OL,19,FCrown could not link the money that
OL,20,Fentered Mitton's accounts with the
OL,21,Fscrap metal firm.
